Heat in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, fry the @British Beef Mince{240%g}, ~{5-6%mins}.

Break up the mince as it cooks, then drain the fat. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook
so there's no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30%g}.

Add the @Mexican Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}, @Tomato Puree{30%g},
@Chicken Stock Paste{10%g}, @Sugar{1%tsp} and @Water{100%ml}(for the sauce)
to the mince. Bring to the boil, then simmer, ~{2-3%mins}.

Meanwhile, slice the @Brioche Hot Dog Buns{2} top down through the middle
(but not all the way through).

In a #bowl{}, combine the @Coleslaw Mix{120%g}, @Baby Leaf Mix{20%g} and
@Mayonnaise{32%g}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> TIP: Don't add the leaves too early or they'll go soggy!

Transfer the hot dog buns to your plates. Fill with the mince. Sprinkle
over the cheese. Serve the baby leaf slaw alongside. Enjoy!